o do the fuce\nlifting job on the story of the\nEgyptian rulers which was first\npresented in connection with Hie\nopening of the Suez Canal.\nU. Oklahoma\u2014\n(concluded irom page 1)\nvis did not enter Meharry because\nhe wanted to \"study in his home\nstate.\" He took his pre-medical\nwoj'k at Lincoln university in Mo.\nTwo Langston university stud\nents were refused admission to\nOklahoma A college, also\nlast week. Miss Jane Carolyn El-\n!is,\nOklahoma City and Henry W.\nFloyd, Eufaula were the reject\nees. Both said they had not made\nnny future plans.\nMiss Ellis said she learned of\nher rejection \"only when I read\nthe paper. I don't think I will\nbe content to continue at Langs\nton, but I don't know yet.\"\nShe was seeking a home econo\nmics course at A while\nFloyd wanted a political science\ndegree. Rejections were based on\nthe grounds that such courses\nwere offered at Langston.\nNews of Dayton\u2014\n(concluded from page 1)\nfour days later. Thirty-four\nothers were granted paroles along\nvvith Creager.\nOBEY SIGNS\nOR\nI\nHEAVY FINES\nA ruling handed down by Coun\ny Prosecutor Malhias Heck, Tues\nday will bring heavy fines and\nprison terms to motorist who vi\nolate the county and state safety\njigns in Montgomery County. Ac\ncording to Heck, the penalties\nwTill run from $10 and 10 days to\n$200 and 30 days. First offend\ners will be liable to fines of $10\nto $50 second offenders from $10\nLo $100 and 10 days in prison or\nboth in within one year third of\nfenders, $25 up to $200 and 30\ndays in prison or both within \u00a9tee\nyear.\nWANT TO BE LEFT ALONE\"\n\"I don't wish to be selfish, not\n*:o contradict the police in their\n'heory that the bombing \\vas the\nwork of any one moving in on my\nbusiness, but am not a well man\naid do wish to be let alone\" was\n\u2022he comment of the retired busi\nness man of Xenia, Ohio, follow\ning a series of phone calls and\ninterviews of the police and press\nin the last three days following\nthe Arti. ioid the? pros\nDR.X2K\nf'9\nOHIO DAILY EXPRESS\n\"I am a retired business man and\nwas self employed when in busi\nness\" and as for being the Num\nbers King in the Miami Valley,\nwell,\nI\ndon't know how that be\u00ad\nlief could have been originated\"\nI don't know of anyone who would\nwant to harm me and as for me\nmoving, well that is out for I\nam not going to move anywhere.\nJIM CRUMP ARRESTED\nJim Crump, alias John Hicks\nand Albert Brown were arrested\nby officers Ralph Hogan and Jim\nPickard, Monday when they re\nvealed numbers slips were intend\ned for operators working out of\nCleveland, Ohio. They were re\nleased on $1000 bonds.\nSPORTS ROUND-UP\nThe Cleveland Indians went\ndown to defeat before the St.\nLouis Browns in their opener\nTuesday by the score of 5-1 as\nBob Feller was jerked in the se\ncond frame after giving up a\ntriple to \"Rookie\" Jack Graham.\nFeller was followed to the hill by\nEarly Wynn, Garcia and the re\nliable Satchel Paige, who struck\noue three of the six men he\nfaced in the final two innings.\nLarry Doby walked and scored the\nlone tally for the Indians on a\nlong fly to the outfield by Mick\ney Vernon. Oreste Minoso wen'\nto pinch hit for Garcia and walk\ned in the seventh.\nROBINSON and CAMPANELLA\nJackie Robinson and Roy Cam\npanella celebrated the Dodger\nGiant opener by slamming home\nruns before some 35,000 fans in\nEbbets field to pace their team\nto a 10-3 win over the Giants.\nLefty Joe Hatten went all the\nway for the Dodgers. Jackie had\na field day with a home run in\nthe left field seats to start the\nfourth frame that sent Larry Jen\nson to the showers after Hank\nBehrman had been disposed of in\nthe earlier innings. Roy Camp\nanella, accounted for three runs\nin the same inning with a home\na hefty homo run into the center\nfield stands to score to mates\nahead of him.\nPatronize Our Advertisers\nDUCKY'S CLEANERS\n925 Denniton Avenue. Phon\u00ab ME 2071\nOwi Specialty\u2014Pick Up and Delivery\nONF |AY SEKVTCF\nWives \"Dig In\"\u2014\n(concluded from page 1)\ncomes the recession of business\nwhich caused the present state\nof employment. In a recent in\nterview o\u00a3 a local firm, the man\nagement told this reporter, \"It is\nregrettable that we are being\nforced to lay off our workers due\nto the lack of orders, but when\nour customers discontinue their\norders, we have no choice.\" When\nasked how long will this condition\nlast? the answer was, \"Your guess\nis as good as ours.\" We have no\nway of telling jujst where it will\nchange.\" During the interview\nthe official brought to my atten\ntion the cancellation of a certain\nproduct requiring more than fif\nty workers to process, which\nmeant that the cancellation would\nrequire the laying off of i y\nmen in the last week end. And\nnow, comes the duty of the house\nwife to rearrange her budget \u2022and\nto cut to the bone, her expenses.\nShe must set up a vigilant watch\nover the small, paycheck brought\nhomo by the family breadwinner.\nTOMORROW: Watching your pur\u00ad\nchases\n660\nprotecting\nincome.\nyour current\nBill Sears\ni a .-a a 2 a s a a\nJ)\n'\u2022AT LASTS\nYou Home Owners, who suffer every winter because you have\nSteel Casement Windows on your home that continually Sweat\nall winter!\nWe Have the Perfect All-Aluminum\nCasement Storm Window\nTo Eliminate the Sweatings of your House Windows.\nThey're Beautiful!\nThey're Efficient!\nThey're Reasonably Priced!\nMade by the World's Foremost Manufacturer of\nAluminum Stor Windows and Doors.\nFree Demonstration at Your Home\nALSCO, Inc.\nWednesday, April 20,1949\nPALACE THEATER\n5th at Williams AD 9631\nWednesday and Thursday\nApril 20 and 21\n\u2022BACKGROUND TO DANGER*\nGeorge Raft\u2014Peter Lorre\nSidney Greenstreet\nand\n\"FEAR IN THE NIGHT\"\nPaul Kelly\u2014Ann Doran\nAdded\u2014Comedy\nilSlSlSMSlfil\nt-oMSlSU\nMADAM MAY\nIf worried^ i-.riw-_xed or in doubt\nabout anyone or anything, unde\ncided where to go and what to do to\ngain success and happiness